---
// Figure: Bounded verification is not surveillance
// Three actors in a row — Holder, Checker, Public service / relying party —
// with Oversight below. Three ideas only: what must flow, what the holder
// can inspect, and the boundary that must not become a cross-service
// behavioural record.
---

<div class="reveal my-12 md:my-16">
  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border overflow-hidden" style="background: rgba(11,11,17,0.6);">
    <div class="p-6 md:p-8">

      <div class="mb-6">
        <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-1">Design boundary</p>
        <h3 class="text-text-primary font-display font-bold text-lg tracking-tight">Bounded verification is not surveillance</h3>
      </div>

      <div class="w-full overflow-x-auto">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 700 280" class="w-full min-w-[520px]" role="img" aria-label="Three actors — holder, checker, and public service — with a holder inspection path and an oversight node below. Nothing in the system should become a cross-service behavioural record.">
          <defs>
            <marker id="vvs-arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
              <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.6)"/>
            </marker>
            <marker id="vvs-arrow-holder" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
              <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="rgba(244,114,182,0.75)"/>
            </marker>
          </defs>

          <!-- Core row: Holder → Checker → Public service -->
          <g>
            <rect x="40" y="70" width="160" height="60" rx="10" fill="rgba(244,114,182,0.08)" stroke="rgba(244,114,182,0.55)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <text x="120" y="98" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.9)" font-family="'Syne', system-ui" font-size="13" font-weight="600">Holder</text>
            <text x="120" y="115" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" font-family="'Inter', system-ui" font-size="10">the person</text>
          </g>

          <g>
            <rect x="270" y="70" width="160" height="60" rx="10" fill="rgba(245,158,11,0.08)" stroke="rgba(245,158,11,0.55)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <text x="350" y="98" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.9)" font-family="'Syne', system-ui" font-size="13" font-weight="600">Checker</text>
            <text x="350" y="115" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" font-family="'Inter', system-ui" font-size="10">verification service</text>
          </g>

          <g>
            <rect x="500" y="70" width="160" height="60" rx="10" fill="rgba(74,222,128,0.08)" stroke="rgba(74,222,128,0.55)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <text x="580" y="98" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.9)" font-family="'Syne', system-ui" font-size="13" font-weight="600">Public service</text>
            <text x="580" y="115" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" font-family="'Inter', system-ui" font-size="10">or relying party</text>
          </g>

          <!-- Forward flow -->
          <line x1="200" y1="100" x2="270" y2="100" stroke="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" stroke-width="1.3" marker-end="url(#vvs-arrow)"/>
          <line x1="430" y1="100" x2="500" y2="100" stroke="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" stroke-width="1.3" marker-end="url(#vvs-arrow)"/>

          <!-- Holder inspection back channel -->
          <path d="M 270 130 Q 195 170 160 130" fill="none" stroke="rgba(244,114,182,0.7)" stroke-width="1.3" stroke-dasharray="4 3" marker-end="url(#vvs-arrow-holder)"/>
          <text x="215" y="175" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(244,114,182,0.85)" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', monospace" font-size="10">holder can inspect</text>

          <!-- Oversight node -->
          <g>
            <rect x="270" y="205" width="160" height="48" rx="10" fill="rgba(167,139,250,0.1)" stroke="rgba(167,139,250,0.6)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <text x="350" y="228" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.9)" font-family="'Syne', system-ui" font-size="13" font-weight="600">Oversight · redress</text>
            <text x="350" y="244" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(232,232,240,0.55)" font-family="'Inter', system-ui" font-size="10">complaints · appeal · audit</text>
          </g>

          <line x1="350" y1="130" x2="350" y2="205" stroke="rgba(167,139,250,0.35)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <!-- Boundary note below, not inside the diagram -->
      <div class="mt-5 pt-4 border-t border-border/40">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-2" style="color: rgba(239,68,68,0.75);">Boundary</p>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Nothing in this flow should become a cross service behavioural record.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs mt-3 text-center italic">
    Bounded verification means only what the use case requires is checked, and only for the purpose at hand. That is not the same thing as surveillance.
  </p>
</div>
